## 1. What it does

Eight independent, idempotent steps per repo:

| Step | What it enforces |
|------|------------------|
| 1 | **Group invites** — share the repo with the 7 LDAP groups at their spec roles |
| 2 | **Push rules** — branch-name regex + commit-message regex |
| 3 | **Protected branches** — `main`, `develop`, `sit-integration`, `release/*`; push = No one |
| 4 | **MR approval rules** — 11 rules, one approver group each |
| 5 | **Pipelines must succeed** before merge |
| 6 | **Merge method** = "Merge commit" |
| 7 | **Squash option** = "Do not allow" |
| 8 | **Default branch** = `main` |

Every step reads current state first and **skips if already correct**, so
re-running is safe and produces no redundant writes.

