## 2. File layout

```
cicd-templates/
├── .gitlab-ci.yml                       # stages + 2 includes. Nothing else.
├── templates/
│   ├── selfvalidate/
│   │   └── selfvalidate.main.yml        # existing lint/validate jobs
│   └── governance/
│       ├── governance.main.yml          # variables + shared base + includes
│       ├── governance.verify.yml        # verify job  (read-only)
│       ├── governance.dryrun.yml        # dry-run job (read-only preview)
│       ├── governance.apply.yml         # apply job   (writes; manual+protected)
│       └── README.md                    # this file
└── scripts/governance/
    └── apply_repo_governance.py         # the script (stdlib only)
```

The two pipelines are fully independent:

| Trigger | selfvalidate jobs | governance jobs |
|---|---|---|
| Normal commit / push | run | **hidden** |
| Run pipeline + `RUN_GOVERNANCE=true` | run | run (per `GOV_MODE`) |

Governance is invisible on normal commits — every governance job defaults to
`when: never` unless `RUN_GOVERNANCE == "true"`.

Only `.gitlab-ci.yml` declares `stages:`. The includes must never declare it,
or they will clobber each other.

