## 3. One-time setup

### 3.1 Commit the files

Commit everything above into
`itepaypg-sbiepay2/infra/devops/cicd-templates`, keeping the paths exactly as
shown. `GOV_SCRIPT` in `governance.main.yml` points at
`scripts/governance/apply_repo_governance.py`.

### 3.2 Add CI/CD variables

`cicd-templates` → **Settings → CI/CD → Variables**:

| Variable | Value | Flags |
|---|---|---|
| `GOVERNANCE_TOKEN` | `glpat-...` | **Masked**, **Protected** |
| `GOVERNANCE_GITLAB_URL` | `https://gitlab.sbi` | Protected |

> ### Token requirement — read this
>
> Must be a **PERSONAL access token** (Avatar → Edit profile → Access Tokens),
> scope `api`, from a user with **Maintainer (40) or Owner (50)** on the target
> repos.
>
> **Group and project access tokens do NOT work.** They authenticate fine and
> pass Steps 1/3/4, then fail Step 2 with `403 Forbidden` on the `/push_rule`
> endpoint. This was confirmed during testing — a token showing
> `"username": "group_2783_bot_...", "bot": true` is a group token and will
> fail.
>
> Verify which kind you have:
> ```bash
> curl -k --header "PRIVATE-TOKEN: <token>" https://gitlab.sbi/api/v4/user
> ```
> `"bot": false` and a real username = personal token = correct.
>
> Set a calendar reminder for the token's expiry.

If `GOVERNANCE_TOKEN` is **Protected**, it is only exposed on protected
branches. Run governance pipelines from `main` (or another protected branch),
or the job fails with `GOVERNANCE_TOKEN CI variable is not set`.

### 3.3 Verify the runner and image

`.governance_base` in `governance.main.yml` uses:

```yaml
image: artifactory.jfrog.sbi:443/itepaypg-sbiepay2-docker-local/custom-ci/rhelgit-oc-helm:1.0
tags:
  - common_runner
```

This matches the existing selfvalidate jobs. The image must contain `python3`
(3.6+). The `before_script` prints `python3 --version` so a missing interpreter
fails loudly on line one rather than mid-run.

