## 6. Reading the output

The `=== VERIFY (read-only) ===` block is the go/no-go. A compliant repo shows:

```
Shared groups (project members):
  epay-gitlab-bank-app-owner: access level 50
  epay-gitlab-bank-app-maintainer: access level 40
  epay-gitlab-vendor-app-maintainer: access level 40
  epay-gitlab-vendor-release-manager: access level 30
  epay-gitlab-vendor-app-lead: access level 30
  epay-gitlab-vendor-app-developer: access level 30
  epay-gitlab-vendor-pm: access level 20
Protected branches:
  main: push=No one | merge groups=[...]
  develop: push=No one | merge groups=[...]
  sit-integration: push=No one | merge groups=[...]
  release/*: push=No one | merge groups=[...]
Approval rules:
  ... 11 rules ...
Project settings:
  Pipelines must succeed : True
  Merge method           : merge (Merge commit)
  Squash option          : never (Do not allow)
  Default branch         : main
Push rules:
  branch_name_regex   : ^(main|develop|sit-integration|...
  commit_message_regex: ^[A-Z]{3}-[0-9]{3}\|[A-Z]{2}\|...
```

Red flags:

| Output | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `<-- expected ...` | that setting did not take |
| `MISSING: <branch>` | branch not protected (usually it does not exist) |
| `MISSING: no push rules set` | Step 2 failed |
| `[WARN] push rules did NOT persist` | both JSON and form-encoded writes failed |
| `push=[{...access_level: 40...}]` | push is NOT "No one" |
| `SKIP '<rule>' (target branch not protected)` | approval rule skipped |

The run log is a **build artifact, 90-day retention** — your audit trail.

Sweep a batch afterwards:
```bat
findstr /C:"MISSING" /C:"WARN" /C:"expected" governance_BATCH_*.txt
```
Zero hits = all repos compliant.

