## 7. The governance spec

### 7.1 LDAP groups

| Group | ID | Project role |
|---|---|---|
| `epay-gitlab-bank-app-owner` | 4953 | Owner (50) |
| `epay-gitlab-bank-app-maintainer` | 4954 | Maintainer (40) |
| `epay-gitlab-vendor-app-maintainer` | 4955 | Maintainer (40) |
| `epay-gitlab-vendor-release-manager` | 4950 | Developer (30) |
| `epay-gitlab-vendor-app-lead` | 4956 | Developer (30) |
| `epay-gitlab-vendor-app-developer` | 4957 | Developer (30) |
| `epay-gitlab-vendor-pm` | 4962 | Reporter (20) |

Groups live under `itepaypg-sbiepay2/ldap-membership/`. IDs are **hardcoded**
because `GET /groups?search=` did not match reliably on this instance. On a new
instance, re-run `find_ldap_groups.py` and update `GROUP_IDS` + `GROUP_INVITES`.

**Step 1 must run before Step 3.** GitLab rejects a protected-branch merge
group that is not already a project member:
`422 Merge access levels group does not have access to the project`.

### 7.2 Protected branches — push = No one on all

| Branch | Allowed to merge |
|---|---|
| `main` | bank-app-maintainer, bank-app-owner, vendor-app-maintainer |
| `develop` | vendor-app-lead, vendor-app-maintainer, vendor-release-manager |
| `sit-integration` | vendor-app-lead, vendor-app-maintainer, vendor-release-manager |
| `release/*` | vendor-app-lead, vendor-app-maintainer, vendor-release-manager |

`feature/*`, `bugfix/*`, `hotfix/*` are intentionally **unprotected** —
developers push freely; governance is enforced at the target branch via
approval rules.

### 7.3 Approval rules (11)

| Target | Rule | Group |
|---|---|---|
| `develop` | Lead Approval | vendor-app-lead |
| `release/*` | Release Gate - Lead | vendor-app-lead |
| `release/*` | Release Manager Approval | vendor-release-manager |
| `release/*` | Release Gate - Architect | vendor-app-maintainer |
| `sit-integration` | Release Gate - Lead (SIT) | vendor-app-lead |
| `sit-integration` | Release Manager Approval (SIT) | vendor-release-manager |
| `sit-integration` | Release Gate - Architect (SIT) | vendor-app-maintainer |
| `main` | Vendor Architect Sign-off | vendor-app-maintainer |
| `main` | Vendor PM Approval (CAB gate) | vendor-pm |
| `main` | Bank Maintainer Approval | bank-app-maintainer |
| `main` | Bank PM Final Gate | bank-app-owner |

All require 1 approval. Rules are separate — no combined counts.

**Rules fire on the TARGET branch, not the source.** So `bugfix/* -> develop`
is covered by *Lead Approval*, and `hotfix/* -> main` by the four `main` rules.
No bugfix- or hotfix-specific rules are needed, and adding them would
double-gate the same MRs.

Rule names must be **unique per project** — hence the `(SIT)` suffixes.

### 7.4 Push rules

**Branch names:**
```
^(main|develop|sit-integration|release/(major|minor)-DM[0-9]+-EPAY-[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+|feature/EPAY-[0-9]+-[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+|bugfix/EPAY-[0-9]+-[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+|hotfix/EPAY-[0-9]+-[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+)$
```

| Valid | Invalid |
|---|---|
| `main` | `feature/login` (no EPAY id) |
| `develop` | `release/1.5.0` (semver no longer allowed) |
| `sit-integration` | `hotfix/1.5.1` (semver no longer allowed) |
| `release/minor-DM2026068056-EPAY-bpcl-refund` | `release/patch-DM123-EPAY-x` (only major/minor) |
| `feature/EPAY-1234-upi-autopay` | `sit_integration` (underscore) |
| `bugfix/EPAY-1299-fix-mandate` | |
| `hotfix/EPAY-6789-fix` | |

**Commit messages:** `TICKET|CC|type: subject`
```
^[A-Z]{3}-[0-9]{3}\|[A-Z]{2}\|(feat|fix|docs|style|refactor|perf|test|chore): .+$
```
- `TICKET` = exactly 3 uppercase letters + `-` + exactly 3 digits
- `CC` = exactly 2 uppercase letters
- pipes are **literal characters** in the message

| Valid | Invalid |
|---|---|
| `EPA-123\|IN\|feat: added payment validation` | `EPAY-1299\|IN\|fix: ...` (4+4) |
| `ABC-456\|UK\|fix: corrected refund rounding` | `EPA-123\|IN\|feat:no space` |
| `XYZ-001\|DC\|chore: bump image version` | `EPA-123 IN feat: ...` (no pipes) |
| | `feat: old format EPAY-123` |

GitLab evaluates these with **RE2** server-side. RE2 has no lookahead,
lookbehind, or backreferences — these patterns use none.

### 7.5 Project settings

| Setting | Value | API field |
|---|---|---|
| Pipelines must succeed | `true` | `only_allow_merge_if_pipeline_succeeds` |
| Merge method | Merge commit | `merge_method: "merge"` |
| Squash | Do not allow | `squash_option: "never"` |
| Default branch | `main` | `default_branch` |

> **Merge method is load-bearing.** The semver/tagging logic parses merge-commit
> titles on `main` to resolve the source branch. Changing away from
> "Merge commit" breaks it **silently**.

