## 8. Safety model

| Control | Effect |
|---|---|
| `RUN_GOVERNANCE != "true"` | no governance job is created at all |
| `GOV_MODE=verify` / `dryrun` | read-only; cannot change anything |
| `GOV_MODE=apply` | requires protected branch **and** manual click |
| apply from unprotected branch | job never offered (`when: never`) |
| `GOV_TARGET` empty | `before_script` guard aborts |
| `GOVERNANCE_TOKEN` empty | `before_script` guard aborts |
| every write | targets `/projects/<id>/...` only — never a group endpoint |
| every step | idempotent — reads state, skips if correct |
| multi-repo | **fail-stop** on first error |
| group ID validation | aborts before any write if a group is unreachable |
| Step 8 | only sets default branch if that branch **exists** |
| run log | 90-day artifact for audit |

Subgroup mode's only write path is per-project. Listing a subgroup's projects
is a read-only `GET`.

