## 9. Troubleshooting

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `401 Unauthorized` | Wrong instance, or expired/invalid token | Check the banner says `gitlab.sbi`, not `gitlab.epay.sbi`. Tokens are instance-specific. |
| `403 Forbidden` on Step 2 only | Group/project access token | Use a **personal** access token |
| `403 Forbidden` everywhere | Token lacks Maintainer/Owner | Check role on the project |
| `GOVERNANCE_TOKEN is not set` | Protected variable + unprotected branch | Run from `main`, or untick Protected |
| `GOV_TARGET is empty` | Variable not provided | Always set `GOV_TARGET` |
| `Project not found` | Wrong path / case / instance | Use the numeric ID |
| `Subgroup not found` | Wrong group path | Use the numeric group ID |
| Job stuck pending | Runner tag mismatch | Check `.governance_base.tags` |
| `python3: command not found` | Image lacks python3 | Use an image that has it |
| No governance job appears | `RUN_GOVERNANCE` not exactly `true` | Check spelling/case |
| `script config should be a string...` | Unquoted `(` `)` in a script line | Quote every script line |
| `stage does not exist` | An include declared `stages:` | Only `.gitlab-ci.yml` may |
| `422 Merge access levels group does not have access` | Step 1 skipped | Group must be a member before Step 3 |
| `allowed_to_merge is invalid` | Form-encoded nested array | Script sends JSON — already handled |
| `404` on push rules | Plural `push_rules` endpoint | Endpoint is singular `push_rule` — already handled |

### Useful diagnostics

```bash
# What kind of token is this? ("bot": true = group token = will fail Step 2)
curl -k --header "PRIVATE-TOKEN: <token>" https://gitlab.sbi/api/v4/user

# Can it read push rules on this project? (200 = yes)
curl -k -i --header "PRIVATE-TOKEN: <token>" https://gitlab.sbi/api/v4/projects/2840/push_rule

# What access levels exist on the project?
curl -k --header "PRIVATE-TOKEN: <token>" https://gitlab.sbi/api/v4/projects/2840/members/all
```

